---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { getLangFromUrl, useTranslations, getNavLink } from '../utils/i18n';

const lang = getLangFromUrl(Astro.url);
const t = useTranslations(lang);
---

<Layout title={`${t('nav.faq')} | ${t('site.title')}`} description={t('meta.faq.description')}>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header text-center mb-4">
        <h1>Get Your Questions Answered</h1>
        <p class="text-large">Everything you need to know about saving 20+ hours per week with AI automation</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-container">
        <div class="faq-category">
          <h2>How It Works</h2>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>How does Espai.ai actually save me time?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Our AI records all your processes, identifies repetitive tasks, and builds custom automations that eliminate manual work. Most companies save 20+ hours per week - that's like hiring an extra employee without the overhead.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>Is my data safe and private?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Absolutely. Your data never leaves your systems and is never seen by humans. We only use it to build automations for you. If we ever want to use your data for anything else, we'll ask for your explicit permission first.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>How quickly will I see results?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Most companies start seeing time savings during the second or fourth month, depending on the sector and complexity of processes. Our AI needs time to analyze your processes and build effective automations. You'll get detailed reports showing exactly how much time each automation saves.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-category">
          <h2>Pricing & ROI</h2>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>What's the real cost and ROI?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>You pay €70-100 per device per month, plus small fees per automation. If you save just 20 hours per week (our average), that's worth €2,000+ per month in employee time. Most companies see ROI during the second or fourth month, depending on the sector and complexity of processes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>What if I don't see any savings?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>You don't pay anything until automations start saving you time. If we can't deliver results, you don't pay. It's that simple. We're confident we can help you save time, or you don't pay.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>Can I cancel anytime?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes, no long-term contracts. You can cancel anytime, though most clients see such significant savings they never want to stop. Once you see how much time you're saving, you'll wonder how you ever worked without it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-category">
          <h2>Implementation</h2>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>How complicated is the setup?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Not complicated at all. We handle everything: installation, configuration, and automation development. You don't need any technical knowledge. Just let us know when you're ready to start saving time.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>What kind of support do you provide?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>We provide full support throughout the entire process. From initial setup to ongoing optimization, our team is here to help. Pro and Pro Advanced plans include priority support and dedicated account managers.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>Will this disrupt my current workflow?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>No disruption at all. Our software runs silently in the background, recording processes without interfering with your work. Automations are implemented gradually and only after thorough testing to ensure they work perfectly.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-category">
          <h2>Results & Success</h2>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>What kind of results do other companies see?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Our clients save an average of 20+ hours per week. That's 1,040+ hours per year - equivalent to hiring an additional full-time employee. Many companies also report improved accuracy and reduced errors.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>How do you measure success?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>We track actual time spent on tasks before and after automation. You get detailed reports showing exactly how much time each automation saves, plus metrics on accuracy improvements and error reduction.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span>What if I need custom automations?</span>
              <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>We build custom automations for your specific needs. Our AI analyzes your unique processes and creates tailored solutions. Pro Advanced plans include complex workflow automation and custom integrations.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="cta-section text-center mt-4">
        <h2>Ready to Start Saving Time?</h2>
        <p class="text-large">Get your free process analysis and see how much time you can save</p>
        <a href={getNavLink('contact', lang)} class="btn">Get Free Analysis</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .faq-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  
  .faq-category {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }
  
  .faq-category h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--accent);
  }
  
  .faq-item {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .faq-item:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
  
  .faq-question {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    border: none;
    color: var(--space-white);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-align: left;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .faq-question:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
  }
  
  .faq-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--accent);
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .faq-answer {
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  
  .faq-answer.active {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    max-height: 1000px;
  }
  
  .faq-item.active .faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }
  
  .contact-section {
    background: radial-gradient(circle at center, rgba(6, 182, 212, 0.1) 0%, transparent 70%);
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
    border-radius: 16px;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .faq-question {
      padding: 1rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    
    .faq-answer.active {
      padding: 1rem;
      max-height: 1000px;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  function toggleFaq(button) {
    const faqItem = button.parentElement;
    const answer = faqItem.querySelector('.faq-answer');
    
    // Close all other FAQ items
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(item => {
      if (item !== faqItem) {
        item.classList.remove('active');
        item.querySelector('.faq-answer').classList.remove('active');
      }
    });
    
    // Toggle current FAQ item
    faqItem.classList.toggle('active');
    answer.classList.toggle('active');
  }
  
  // Make function global
  window.toggleFaq = toggleFaq;
</script> 